Author: TimTam2017
Title: [ANN][ICO] ðŸ”· SELFPAY.ASIA ICO ðŸ”· LIVE IN JULY ðŸ”· 20% BONUS THE FIRST WEEK
Body: Yeah, I think we can safely assume this was a huge scam!  If you Google Julien Chalte in the news, you also get this : https://www.nouvelobs.com/politique/20151028.OBS8477/le-cabinet-noir-de-la-sarkozie-finalement-condamne.html  Now I don't speak French, but a quick Google translate shows that the guy was involved in dark places in French politics... I would not be surprised if he just left France because he was blacklisted over there. Julien Chalte is clearly a scammer and dangerous.  Raphael Tant is a scammer too I think. I managed to talk with an ex-team member a few months ago, he would not chat with me because he did not want anything in written. What he said on the phone was that basically, when the ether were raised, there were promises made by Raphael that were never kept. For him, it started to look like Raphael wanted to scam everybody and keep the money and run with it, so he left the company.  Looks like it's exactly what Raphael did. Pathetic. But what did you expect from people who are apparently mixed with shady individuals. Hopefully nobody invested large sums in this project.

Selfpay will have its own blockchain in Q4 2018     - Selfpay team will migrate all SxP ECR20 token to Selfpay Blockchain on 1:1 ratio  6. Selfpay is mainly focus on Southeast Asia countries  7. Selfpay has stated that it is NOT security but as unity according to their lawyers  8. Selfpay has said that they will not use "buy back" program but instead use masternode rewards    9. Selfpay will have their own exchange in 2019

Body: Total of SXP is 10,000,000, so if you want to estimate how much each SXP token worth in USD, you probably want to compare coins that has near 10,000,000 supply. In this case GAS, Augur fit this mold. Gas has 10,128,375 circulating but has 17,190,378 total supply. As to Augur, it is 11,000,000 with no total supply.  Gas = $11.23  Argur= $31.49  I picked this coins for two reasons,  1. in top 100  2. not a scam, unlikely to fail  So, I'm going to assume that each SxP token price will range between $20 to $50. The reason is that not all 10,000,000 will be on the market which means less supply. Selfpay reserve 20% for the team member/partners  which leaves out 80%, that is 8,000,000 token. Not all 8,000,000 will be on the market, let say half of the token holder decided to sell, so basically that is about 4,000,000.  If you are token holder, you could make passive income through masternode. I'm not sure how everything works

Author: Julien_Chalte
Title: [ANN][ICO] ðŸ”· SELFPAY.ASIA ICO ðŸ”· LIVE IN JULY ðŸ”· 20% BONUS THE FIRST WEEK
Body: Thank you for your opinion, all feedbacks matter to us. I have one question though: why are you so bitter if you got a refund already? Which, by the way, proves that we are not a scam, right?  Despite what you think, yes, some discussions take a very long time to close. But it's not only about these discussions, as explained in our latest Medium article.  Now let me explain you a few things: this is a business. Like every business, sometimes industry parameters change, and we have to adapt. You said "more cool features? don't need cool features". Really? I thought an ICO was about building a solid long term project, not flipping coins at the listing on exchanges. At least that's what we're working on here: building a service that people will like and use. The ICO is just a means to this end, let's just be clear on that.  A year after Pre-ICO? So what? There is no predefined timeline for each step of a life cycle of a company. As much as I do understand the impatience it might trigger for some of you, we have to do what's best for the company, with no personal emotions involved, from any side. This is the wisest approach, and the most long term viable option.  Let me ask you this, and I wish to get an honest answer from you: should we rush, burn all the ETH we got to try and do a quick & cheap ICO, just to say we did it? Or wait until the market recovers a little to spend our contributors' money wisely and responsibly?

Author: bitcoinbelieve
Title: [ANN][ICO] ðŸ”· SELFPAY.ASIA ICO ðŸ”· LIVE IN JULY ðŸ”· 20% BONUS THE FIRST WEEK
Body: People should not invest lots of money in this project b/c there is so much unknown factors. Example, Selfpay sent out this email in Oct 2017.    Dear Subscriber,  This is an official announcement from the SelfPay's team.  Given the recent regulation issues related to tokens that are considered as securities, the fact that most of the exchanges are now reluctant to accept such tokens, and also to make sure that SXP token holders will always find a buyer when they want to sell their token,  we have decided to set up a buy back program  to replace the previous model based on profit sharing.  As a direct consequence of this, we have decided to reduce the number of SxP in circulation in order to sustain the buyback program. While the percentage of distribution remains the same, the maximum supply will be reduced from 100 million to 10 million.  The good news for the token holders is that it will ensure the token will be sold at a minimum price of 300 SxP for 1 ETH, and also, as less tokens are in circulation, prices are likely increase.  To give you an example, while before, with 10,000 SXP, a token holder was holding 0.1 % of the total SXP tokens, with the new system, this same token holder will hold 1% of the total token supply, so  10 times more  than before !  Finally, we are also making another change to make sure that SxP tokens are going to appreciate in value. SxP tokens will also be accepted as a form of payment, at SxP market price, by our network of merchants, ensuring that contributors will be able to buy on our market place using the SxP token without having to pay any fees.  The English version of our whitepaper has been updated to reflect those changes, feel free to have a look.

Author: Julien_Chalte
Title: [ANN][ICO] ðŸ”· SELFPAY.ASIA ICO ðŸ”· LIVE IN JULY ðŸ”· 20% BONUS THE FIRST WEEK
Body: Oh... You again It's been a while! Just a quick question before I start: do you have any personal feud against us or against a member of our team? I mean, come on, creating a profile solely to intervene here and throw some FUD... Well, anyone enjoys spending his time as he wishes, after all     We can't control who comes and go, it's a public forum. We are indeed increasing our reach and this must be a consequence of it.   Also, I am just baffled that they have not changed their prices. I already believed 300 tokens for 1ETH was high when the ETH was worth around US$ 200, now that the value has tripled, their token is still worth the same? That means the token value is around US$ 2? When very successful tokens like Ripple started at US$ 0.0X? That must be a joke, right?  You do know that what matters is not the price per token but the total market cap, right? A bit like the price of a company share, where the total number of shares multiplied by its unit price defines the company's market cap, and then, supply and demand playing its magic, the price goes up or down, regardless of the supply (as long as it's fixed to avoid dilution). And for a project like SelfPay with all its regional implications, a total market cap of a bit more than 33,300 ETH is definitely reasonable. But, I shouldn't be telling you this, you should be well documented on that topic before saying nonsense, right?   This is my personal opinion but I'd stay away from that project, not convincing at all, and I am not sure the team knows what they are doing.  Oh, based on the nonsense you said before? Right.   I am curious too, what if the ICO sales fails to reach the minimum cap? Will they reimburse people from the preICO sales too? Because if not, I will say it again, it looks to me they're just trying to do an ICO knowing it'll fail, keep the previous found, and go "oh well, it did not work, bye bye"    We're not keeping any funds for ourselves, we're utilizing it as any regular company would do, to run its operations. But... Do you know how it works? I'm a little bit in doubt, based on your previous (scary) assumptions.

Body: You can call him a troll if you want, but looks like a lot of different users are telling you your ICO smells bad. Why pick on him in particular? To deflect and not answer other's concern?  I want to believe your "marketing efforts" are "rolling out", but all I can see is a twitter account that got 1 post who was liked by yourself, a telegram community who is getting smaller by the day, and a Facebook page that has no post and that for whatever reason is not even linked on your website anymore.  Now we can be wrong, and please, show us what your marketing efforts are if you have done any, but for the moment, it seems like you are doing what the user target mentioned: walk away with the funds you raised on your pre ICO, which is a shame, because that is basically scamming people.

Author: Julien_Chalte
Title: [ANN][ICO] ðŸ”· SELFPAY.ASIA ICO ðŸ”· LIVE IN JULY ðŸ”· 20% BONUS THE FIRST WEEK
Body: Hello,  RaphaÃ«l officially introduced me to you all last month, and I am really thrilled to join this project.  Please allow me to tell you with a bit more details what we are working on at the moment:  Having a great project, addressing real needs, is one thing. Making it happen by complying to all laws and regulations, already in place or anticipating upcoming ones, another.  This is what is currently taking most of our time. Regulations. Setting up a proper entity to make sure that the ICO will be legit, recognized as such, not seen as falling under any Securities laws, and so on.  So today, I am happy to announce, after having worked countless hours with our legal council during these past few weeks, that the ICO will take place under the Singaporean jurisdiction.  Why Singapore? In short: they already have strict regulations in place regarding ICOs and cryptocurrencies in general, and the Thai government has good ties with Singapore (SelfPay is based in Bangkok, where the whole team resides).  To emphasize that, I would like to quote a portion of this article, dated 28th March: https://www.bangkokpost.com/business/finance/1436159/draft-decree-on-digital-assets-approved     As for the ICO date, we can now confirm that it will happen next month, in May. The exact day still needs to be confirmed, though. But we will announce it officially as soon as it has been set.  Thank you for your trust. Stay tuned!

Author: SelfPay - Kevin
Title: [ANN][ICO] ðŸ”· SELFPAY.ASIA ICO ðŸ”· LIVE IN JULY ðŸ”· 20% BONUS THE FIRST WEEK
Body: I am not sure which question you are referring to regarding dividends, but in a general way, it was the plan to offer rewards based on the revenues of the company. These could have been considered dividends, and when we started our project, there was no problem with this kind of system. But recently, regulations have happened, and anything that could be considered securities (included dividends then) are very sensitive and most of the time illegal. Because of this, we had to change our way of approaching the reward for our contributors to make sure there wouldn't be any problems. We then decided to put in place a Buy Back system.

Body: Each months, one of the millions of Ã‰lectricitÃ© du Laos (EDL) consumers need to pay their electricity bill.  To do so, the user will need to drive dozens of kilo-meters to the local bank (BCEL) only to be met by a one hour queue of other people also trying to pay their electricity bill at the same time.  Tomorrow, this customer can use one of the gift crypto cards that anybody can purchase in any affiliated convenience store or petrol station and pay their electricity bill using only their smartphone.  Tomorrow, thanks to the SelfPay ICO, on each transaction, the seller will receive 20% of the transaction fees as Ethereum and the SxP token holder will receive 40%, thus making the seller and the token holder satisfied.

Title: [ANN][ICO] ðŸ”· SELFPAY.ASIA ICO ðŸ”· LIVE IN JULY ðŸ”· 20% BONUS THE FIRST WEEK
Body: PRE ICO The SxP token PRE SALE will last for 30 days, starting 9:30am UTC on the 3rd of October 2017.  During the PRE SALE only 0.96% of the token will be created with a BONUS of 60% for each token bought.  This PRE SALE will help us to fund a big marketing campaign for the ICO itself.  ICO The SxP token creation will last for 30 days, starting 9:30am UTC on the 3rd of November 2017. A fixed number will be created during the sale and no more will be created thereafter.  SelfPay aims to accept up to 250,000 ETH from our initial token partners and create approximately 40m SxP for sale in exchange for the ETH committed.  The SxP smart contract will stop accepting commitments at 420 000 ETH hard cap. The Token Sale will last for 30 days. If the soft-cap is reached, the event will be extended for 7 days and then closed. If the hard-cap is reached, the event will close automatically.

Author: poordeveloper
Title: [ANN][ICO] ðŸ”· SELFPAY.ASIA ICO ðŸ”· LIVE IN JULY ðŸ”· 20% BONUS THE FIRST WEEK
Body: Yes, SelfPay can also be used on B2B transactions.  As it is the case with many sellers, they buy their stock from a wholesaler, and very often in cash in Asia.  This limits the sellers in terms of the volume they can buy, and slows down their development.  Using SelfPay would allow them to use their credit card to buy bigger volumes from the wholesaler, thus allowing them to sell more and create a virtuous circle.

You do not need to carry too much cash with you, and avoid handing over the wrong amount of money when you pay because you do not know the currency very well. It feels safer and more convenient.

Title: [ANN][ICO] ðŸ”· SELFPAY.ASIA ICO ðŸ”· LIVE IN JULY ðŸ”· 20% BONUS THE FIRST WEEK
Body: Virtually any vendors who wishes to use it. Let's take the example of a taxi driver.  Many of us have wished that they could pay their ride via credit/debit card.  That is one of the reason why some of the new car sharing app are so popular.  The issue is that, they tend to be more expensive than a normal taxi ride. Tomorrow, with SelfPay, your usual taxi driver will send you a payment link, and youâ€™ll be able to pay from your phone with your card. And since the payments are real time, the whole process will be quick.

Body: In Southeast Asia, many people sell via Facebook or Instagram for example. They are very good platforms to display pictures of the products you sell, descriptions, and basically allows you to not have to invest money and time into developing an ecommerce platform. The only issue right now for these sellers is payment.  They often have to either meet face to face to collect the money in cash, or ask for a bank transfer, wait until the transfer appears, then send the goods. It is a tedious process.  On the other side, people buying from social sellers canâ€™t use their credit card, and if they canâ€™t afford that good they want so much, will give up.  SelfPay would allow the social sellers to just have to send a payment link to the buyer and in a minute, they can confirm the payment and send the item. Buyers can also use their credit card and acquire a good even if they do not have the funds yet.

Author: SelfPay - Kevin
Title: [ANN][ICO] ðŸ”· SELFPAY.ASIA ICO ðŸ”· LIVE IN JULY ðŸ”· 20% BONUS THE FIRST WEEK
Body: Thank you for a very good question ! In terms of payments, when it's online or in small shops, people are still reluctant to pay by card in Southeast Asia. Not because they can't, but because of the trust factor. Think about Europe and the US a decade ago, when internet payments started to be the norm. At first, people were still hesitant to make payments online because they could not trust that everything would be ok. Now people don't think about it that much.  Well, Southeast Asia is still in that phase where the trust for online payments is not there. The same goes with shops that are not big renowned chains.  SelfPay will help with this because everything happens on the buyer's device when it comes to payment.

Author: SelfPay - Kevin
Title: [ANN][ICO] ðŸ”· SELFPAY.ASIA ICO ðŸ”· LIVE IN JULY ðŸ”· 20% BONUS THE FIRST WEEK
Body: Hi, thank you for the question.  The MVP is actually fully functioning and has been tested in a couple of countries in Southeast Asia. The technology behind is solid. The release planned Q4 is more for marketing and awareness. Our ultimate goal to allow payments in crypto will happen later though, and the main challenge won't be totally on the technology side, but more on the user behavior's side.

Author: silverthornne
Title: [ANN][ICO] ðŸ”· SELFPAY.ASIA ICO ðŸ”· LIVE IN JULY ðŸ”· 20% BONUS THE FIRST WEEK
Body: Beside that and similarly to other projects that also give some share on the profit, the ERC20 smart contract provide a burn function.  Which means that at any time, a holder of SxP can â€œRedeem and Burnâ€ the SxP for their pro-rata share of each token held by the SxP Asset Contract.  Doing so the holder will irrevocably destroy the SxP, and in exchange, the SxP Asset Contract will transfer the underlying tokens to the holder.  It ensures that the SxP token will have a market value at or above the assets contained in the SxP Asset Contract.  If the value goes below, market participants will be incentivised to purchase SxP and burn it which will then push the value of SxP back up.

Body: Apology for not having answered before to your question and thank you for asking.  Monetha.  Monetha address only online seller and accept only cryptocurrency. The retail product shall be available mid late 2019.  SelfPay.  SELFPAY, provide payment services for Online and Offline business, the sellers do not need to have a web site to use our solution which include a mobile point of sell. Of course, Selfpay provide also online payment.  SELFPAY already accept payment in credit card/debit card,  the seller crypto back reward is coded as we speak as well as the crypto payment, which is really easy to code compared to credit card payment.  Our product for retailer is ready and will be spread in South East Asia post ico, beginning of 2018   To resume, from a product perspective  SELFPAY product cover most, if not all, seller use cases  and also is addressing online and offline business The product already exist, no need to wait 2019 to have it.  From an investor perspective  SELFPAY market is bigger than Monetha, we are addressing online and offline business, existing debit and credit card consumers and of course crypto payments. We are targeting South East Asia first so not the same market size and not the same consumer. The SxP token have a burn and redeem functionality, ensuring that the token price will always goes up.

Author: silverthornne
Title: [ANN][ICO] ðŸ”· SELFPAY.ASIA ICO ðŸ”· LIVE IN JULY ðŸ”· 20% BONUS THE FIRST WEEK
Body: Thank you for your question, I am glad you ask it, let me can show you something that I really like in SelfPay:    The separation of trust   The buyer receive a paylink and use his own phone to pay.  The seller get 20% of the transaction fees reward in crypto, and 40% goes to the SxP Token holder.  The seller is happy to get a selling reward, and he is even more happy to use the solution again !  Keep in mind that  any seller can use the solution, even in brick and mortar shop, it s not just a new online payment, the seller do not need to have a web site to use it, it is a far bigger market than just the online market, this is something new and fresh !  As far as I am concern, there is a lot of competitor on the online payment space, but I failed to find any competitor that : offer a offline and online fiat payment and reward the sellers by using crypto currency.  Don't take me wrong, Today, while I am writing those lines I am sure that other companies will have the same idea, but for now there is none that offer the same advantages than SelfPay.  Kindly read the whitePaper it explain the concept with much more details  and give daily use case of the solution  https://ico.selfpay.asia/whitepaper.html

Body: From my perspective this has little impact to the project on itself. From the beginning the team believe that credit card payments are not going to disappear over night, so the profit sharing from the transaction fees that token holders and merchant get will not change - no impact here.  On the other hand, we can also imagine that a number of Chinese people that are holding crypto currency at the moment would be happy to directly pay SelfPay network of merchants in crypto currency all over Southeast Asia, which is where the main marketing efforts will be.  If China decides to prohibit ICO and also crypto currencies, it will be probably very sad, but it might even be beneficial for other projects that are not in China such as SelfPay.
